## "Runs since last retro" algorithm
```
runs := store.List(ctx, "refs/etude/runs")        // []ref
retros := store.List(ctx, "refs/etude/retros")    // []ref
var maxRetro time.Time
var lastRetroID string
for each retro ref:
  read manifest; if Created.After(maxRetro): maxRetro = Created; lastRetroID = id
count := 0
for each run ref:
  read manifest
  if maxRetro.IsZero() || Created.After(maxRetro): count++
return count, lastRetroID, nil
```
Any I/O error returns the error to the caller; `emitRetroNudge` swallows it.

## Decision logic
```
// Stale-snooze invalidation: if a new retro has landed since the snooze
// was written (LastRetroIDAtSnooze != current lastRetroID), drop the
// snooze entirely. Otherwise apply it.
snoozedActive := snoozePresent &&
    snooze.LastRetroIDAtSnooze == lastRetroID &&
    (RunsSinceLastRetro - snooze.RunsAtSnooze) < snooze.SnoozeFor

overdue := Enabled && RunsSinceLastRetro >= Threshold
WouldEmit := overdue && !snoozedActive

// Status emits SnoozedUntilRuns = snooze.RunsAtSnooze + snooze.SnoozeFor when
// snoozedActive, else 0. SnoozedAt is the snooze time when active, zero else.
```

## Stderr line format
```
etude: retro nudge: <N> bead(s) since last retro (threshold <T>); run `etude retro generate workflow` or `etude retro nudge dismiss` to silence for now
```
Single newline at end.

## Root command wiring
- Use cobra's `cmd.Find(args)` to resolve the actual command that ran,
  rather than string-matching `args`. Compute skip via the resolved
  command:
  - Resolved command is the root command (no real subcommand) → skip.
  - Resolved command's `Name()` (or any ancestor's name) is `help`,
    `completion`, `__complete`, or `__completeNoDesc` → skip (covers
    cobra-auto-registered shell-completion and help subcommands).
  - The `--help`, `-h`, or `--version` flag is set on the resolved
    command after parsing → skip.
  - Resolved command's full path (Use words from root → leaf) is
    `etude retro nudge` or any of its descendants (`dismiss`, `status`)
    → skip. This silences the entire `retro nudge` subtree so a
    `status` JSON dump on stdout is never accompanied by a stderr
    nudge line.
- Otherwise call `emitRetroNudge` after `cmd.Execute()` (regardless of
  err). PostRun hooks won't fire on subcommand failure, so the call
  must live in `ExecuteWithWriters`.
- `emitRetroNudge` ordering (cheap-checks-first so disabled repos do
  zero ref I/O):
  1. Read `.etude/workflow.yaml`; if missing/malformed → silent return.
  2. Parse + `wf.NudgeEnabled()`; if false → silent return BEFORE
     touching the refstore.
  3. `CountRunsSinceLastRetro` + `ReadSnooze`.
  4. `Decide`; on `WouldEmit` write a single line to `errOut`.
  5. Any error along the way → silent return; the nudge never
     surfaces an error of its own.

