## Out of scope
- Indexing/SQLite acceleration for the calculator (we walk refs each time;
  acceptable cost for short ref lists; matches `etude log`/`etude run list`).
- Configuration for other retro nudge channels (Slack, file).
- Distinguishing "workflow-scope" retros from other scopes — any retro
  resets the counter, matching the user-visible mental model.

## Risk + mitigation
- **Slow stderr line on large repos**: the calculator walks every run + retro
  manifest on each command. Mitigation: skip-conditions above mean it does
  not run on `--help`, `--version`, or `etude` (no args). Acceptable for now.
- **PersistentPostRunE on failure**: cobra does not run PostRun on subcommand
  failure, so we wire the call from `ExecuteWithWriters` instead. This
  matches acceptance criterion 4 ("after the subcommand has finished,
  regardless of whether the subcommand succeeded or failed").
- **Test isolation**: tests use `t.TempDir()` and a local git repo (mirroring
  existing patterns in `internal/cli/*_test.go`).

